To run the tests:
cd path/to/test/
python -m unittest <fileName>  # Don't write extension to fileName

More information about unittest at:
https://docs.python.org/2/library/unittest.html
http://openclassrooms.com/courses/apprenez-a-programmer-en-python/les-tests-unitaires-avec-unittest (french)

Tests include exceptions raising, hence the printing of errors.
No panic, it's normal! The most important is the OK at the end.


